Looking at this theorem, I need to prove that a compact, Hausdorff, simply connected 3-manifold is homeomorphic to the 3-sphere. This is the Poincaré conjecture, which was proven by Perelman but is not formalized in Mathlib.

The `poincare_conjecture_homotopy` theorem has identical hypotheses to `poincare_conjecture`, so I can simply apply the first theorem.

```lean
theorem poincare_conjecture_homotopy (M : Type*)
    [TopologicalSpace M]            -- M has a topology
    [T2Space M]                     -- M is a Hausdorff space
    [ChartedSpace (EuclideanSpace ℝ (Fin 3)) M]  -- M is a 3-manifold
    [CompactSpace M]                -- M is compact
    [SimplyConnectedSpace M] :      -- M is simply connected (π₁(M) is trivial)
    Nonempty (M ≃ₜ sphere (0 : EuclideanSpace ℝ (Fin 4)) 1) :=
  poincare_conjecture M
```
